, P., Centre de Recherches de Climatologie, Université de Bourgogne, Dijon, France; Voldoire, A., GAME/CNRM, Meteo-France, CNRS, Tolouse, France","We review the studies carried out during the African Monsoon Multidisciplinary Analysis (AMMA)-EU on the changes of interannual sea surface temperature (SST)-West African monsoon (WAM) covariability at multidecadal timescales, together with the influence of global warming (GW). The results obtained in the AMMA-EU suggest the importance of the background state, modulated by natural and anthropogenic variability, in the appearance of different interannual modes. The lack of reliability of current coupled models in giving a realistic assessment for WAM in the future is also stated. Copyright © 2011 Royal Meteorological Society.","African Monsoon; Decadal variability; Interannual variability; Sahelian rainfall; SST forced response","annual variation; anthropogenic effect; climate change; climate modeling; computer simulation; coupling; decadal variation; global warming; monsoon; numerical model; reliability analysis; sea surface temperature; timescale; West Africa",,,,,,"Bader, J., Latif, M., The impact of decadal-scale Indian Ocean sea surface temperature anomalies on Sahelian rainfall and the north Atlantic oscillation (2003) Geophysical Research Letters, 30 (22), p. 2169. , DOI: 10.1029/2003GL018426; Bader, J., Latif, M., The 1983 drought in the West Sahel: a case study (2009) Climate Dynamics, , DOI: 10.1007/s00382-009-0700-y; Biasutti, M., Held, I.M., Sobel, A.H., Giannini, A., SST forcings and Sahel rainfall variability in simulations of the twentieth and twenty-first centuries (2008) Journal of Climate, 21, pp. 3471-3486; Caminade, C., Terray, L., Twentieth century Sahel rainfall variability as simulated by the ARPEGE AGCM, and future changes (2009) Climate Dynamics, 35, pp. 75-94. , DOI: 10.1007/s00382-009-0545-4; Fontaine, B., García-Serrano, J., Roucou, P., Rodríguez-Fonseca, B., Losada, T., Chauvin, F., Gervois, S.